The architecture I'm proposing in my head:

CAT6 → Switch → RPi's ethernet port (RPi gets internet from main router)
RPi uses your USB WiFi adapter to broadcast a small hotspot
MIFI's "Internet Wi-Fi" connects to that RPi hotspot as its upstream
MIFI recreates 192.168.100.x exactly as before
MIFI's ethernet port → CAT5e → Compaq → 192.168.100.100 ✓ stable ethernet ✓
Laptop connects to MIFI_6034 WiFi as usual
